author: Oliver Holmes
message: A man may fulfil the object of his existence by asking a question he cannot answer, and attempting a task he cannot achieve.
title: Thought of the day

author: Confucius
message: I am not bothered by the fact that I am unknown. I am bothered when I do not know others.
title: Thought of the day

author: Epictetus
message: He is a wise man who does not grieve for the things which he has not, but rejoices for those which he has.
title: Thought of the day

author: Pablo Picasso
message: I am always doing that which I cannot do, in order that I may learn how to do it.
title: Thought of the day
